In re Kavanagh’s Estate. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 14, 1890.)

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

No opinion. There has not as yet been such loches as would justify the dismissal of these appeals. Motion denied. See 5 N. Y. Supp. 676, 6 N. Y. Supp. 669, and ante, 443.
